The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Wednesday, August 17, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 Ananda Das, Premdip Chatterjee, Raktim Sadhu and Biswajit Mondal qualified from Bengal to be on the BCCI panel of scorers and statisticians for the upcoming season. The examination was conducted in the city from June 27 to July 1 at the B.C. Roy clubhouse. Now Bengal have five representatives in the BCCI panel with the other two being Kaushik Saha and Gautam Roy. 

 After Ranadeep Moitra joined East Bengal as a fitness trainer, CAB has appointed Chinmoy Roy as the Bengal senior team?s fitness trainer. He was officially informed about the appointment on Tuesday.

 Renowned cricket coach Surajit Mukherjee (commonly known as Bulan) passed away on Monday following a cardiac arrest. His wards include players like Safi Ahmed, Charanjit Singh, Humza Ferozie, Alokendu Lahiri and many others. He was 42.

 Arup Basak emerged the champion in the men?s singles category of the Cossimbazar Table Tennis Tournament, beating Sourav Sengupta 11-8, 13-11, 8-11, 12-10, 11-5 on Monday. Anusree Saha lifted the women?s crown beating Rajarshi Sha 11-9, 6-11, 11-5, 11-4, 8-11, 11-8.

 About 1077 people donated blood on the Footballer Lovers? day at Netaji Indoor Stadium on Tuesday.

 Barisha AC advanced into the semi-finals of the State Junior Knockout Basketball meet, defeating Tarun Byam Sangha 18-6 on Tuesday.

 Salkia Swimming Association thrashed Self Culture Institute 6-2 in the Dr Sarkar Allen Group Open Waterpolo meet on Tuesday. Taldi Swimming Centre beat Kidderpore Swimming Club 7-4.

 BASKETBALL: State junior knockout meet semi-finals at the WBBA courts from 4 pm.

 FOOTBALL: First division group A and group B matches at various venues from 3.30 pm.

 WATERPOLO: Dr Sarkar Allen Group Open meet from 3.15 pm.




